			<CASNumber>74-87-3</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Methyl chloride (CH3Cl) is a colourless, flammable, toxic gas. It is primarily prepared by the reaction of methanol with hydrogen chloride, but can also be prepared by the chlorination of methane. It is used chiefly as a refrigerant and methylating agent. It is also an abundant halocarbon and the largest source of chlorine in the stratosphere, thus considered an important ozone-depleting gas.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯化甲烷（CH3Cl）是一种无色、易燃的有毒气体。它主要由甲醇与氯化氢反应制得，也可由甲烷氯化制得。它主要用作制冷剂和甲基化剂。它也是一种丰富的卤化碳，是平流层中氯的最大来源，因此被认为是一种重要的臭氧消耗气体。</common:generalComment>
